How crazy of them to allow someone into our room every day to show it for sale (and the room, of course, looked liked we were using it). We even had a baby sleeping while they were marching through.

5. Upon check in, you are told that you should coordinate most service through the management company but they couldn't get anything done and when you did call - you were ofter told to call the front desk directly! Why are we told to go through the LUX service and then only to be told to call the hotel directly. Check In:
This process was seamless and we were even able to check in early! Room layout:
The two King rooms are connected and the two Queen bed Suite is right next door. We stayed in the queen bed suite and gave our key to the girls staying in the two king rooms and everyone was in and out seamlessly! There was more than enough room for everyone!

Cleanliness/Housekeeping:

Overall:

I will definitely be back!

reviews.comments: Beautiful condo in an amazing location… unfortunately the listing neglects to mention the less enticing aspects of the unit nor does the price reflect them.  For starters, the cleaning fee seems a bit ridiculous considering there is no daily housekeeping - $600!  Secondly; if you’re planning on getting some rest and relaxation in the unit think again… there is a huge construction project next door and concrete jackhammering begins promptly at 9am Monday through Friday.  Don’t leave the bedroom blinds open either as I awoke to three strange men on the balcony via scaffolding that were apparently fixing something (although nobody thought to disclose this to me in advance for privacy’s sake!).  The third bedroom’s sink was plugged and rendered the bathroom essentially unusable… don’t leave the balcony doors open either!  One of the bedroom doors was not latched open when I arrived, and the wind from the open balcony door ended up slamming the bedroom door shut…. Which left us to realize that the door cannot be opened from the main living area (only from inside the bedroom oddly enough)… the “concierge” team of the owner was not responsive as it was in the evening of the arrival night, and nobody from the w hotel was in a rush to open the door as we were in the residences section… even the residence concierge told us she would do it herself and then promptly left at 11pm without attempting to open it for us.  It ended up wasting our first night in Miami as it took us nearly 4 hours to get the door unlocked with all my clothes already unpacked inside the bedroom!  All in all, the place itself is wonderful and the w hotel itself is great.  I do not believe it is worth the price though especially given the noise from next door which really should have been disclosed to us.

We are saddened to hear you had a negative experience staying with us. There were some unforeseeable circumstances that made getting in contact with us more difficult than normal, and I can assure you that unforeseeable circumstances don’t happen regularly. The burnt light bulb might have happened while you were there, as we inspect the residences prior to every arrival to make sure everything is working perfectly; however, our maintenace team are on-premises to assist you with any request you have.

This residence is a 1 bedroom plus den, which is what is advertised in the listing. The layout of this residence in particular doesn’t include the bathroom inside the bedrooms, and that is shown in the photos- it’s just outside both rooms. The second bedroom doesn't have a window because it's considered a den; we have it advertised as a den in the listing; however, Airbnb doesn't allow us to enter 1.5 for bedrooms, so the bed configurations is set to 2 while everywhere else within the listing specifies the den. Also, the den has a door and a full size bed that can accommodate 1-2 guests.

We strongly wish you had seen the listing you were booking in more detail so you knew about these features, which are not necessarily bad, but we understand how this could inconvenience you if it wasn't expected. Again, we try to be as transparent and specific as possible when advertising our properties online. We hope you give LRMB a second chance so we can turn this around for you. We have over 60 oceanfront properties in Miami Beach and I’m sure we can accommodate you in one that will meet your needs and wants more appropriately.

Looking forward to having you back soon.

reviews.comments:
This was a most horrible experience both from the hotel side and from the host side. I held off 2 weeks to write this review to afford both the opportunity to make amends for what we dealt with on our "luxury" vacation. Sadly neither felt the obligation to do anything about the pitiful circumstances we dealt with. My family and I were subjected to no elevator service on multiple days and had to walk up and down 19 floors on several occasions. Our alternative was to stay in our rooms with no other means of getting downstairs. Even the service elevators were inoperative. Furthermore we had floods coming down from the floor above into our master bathroom. A situation both the host and hotel was aware of prior to our stay (as per the maintenance dept) and made no mention. The W/D failed to work as well, and the alternative to that was to get housekeeping service in excess of $400.00 per day. This was on top of the over $3,000.00 a night we were paying for our apartment. Worst of all was the lack of responsiveness from Luxury Rentals Miami Beach. While our host greeted us nicely when we arrived, neither he nor his firm were anywhere to be found during the stay when all of the "stuff" hit the fan. We were just left to fend for ourselves.
The hallways leading to our unit were shabby and falling apart. I would strongly recommend AGAINST ever renting a property through Luxury Rentals Miami Beach as they simply fail to live up to their name, nor do they care about their guests once the register has rung. The grounds of the Setai are beautiful and the beach staff warm and friendly - but that was the only positive of the weekend. My family and I had a 4 bedroom apartment and would cross our fingers we could get off the 19th floor. The morning of checkout, when we had our flight home to catch, the elevators were broken again and we were advised to carry our bags down from the 19th floor. At the very last moment the lone service elevator began to work and we narrowly made our plane home. This was not a "luxury" experience and everyone involved pointed the finger at someone else. AirBNB blamed the host, the host blamed Luxury Rentals, Luxury Rentals blamed the Setai, and so on. The bottom line is Luxury Rentals Miami Beach refused to hold itself accountable in any shape or form. Shame on them. My advice to anyone considering to rent through them is take your business elsewhere.

My issues were with Five Star Luxury Travel.

Checkin/Communication: When I arrived the hotel had no record of my reservation and when o tried to contact the host the voicemail was full and my messages were not answered. After a 5 hour flight we had to wait in the lobby over an hour to get this straightened out.

Advertised v. Reality: The actual property was not as pictured. Slightly different unit with missing patio furniture and one bathroom sink instead of two. When you step onto balcony you are looking at a huge construction crane and listening to loud construction noise all day. A major concern is that the hotel collects a pretty hefty daily fee in addition to the bnb fees which drastically changes the price of the actual unit per night price. There is a small blurb about this in the posting, embedded between lots of fluff information so you don’t readily catch this caveat.

The unit had a dingy feel. Decor is all very light so it shows dirt easily and it was not very clean. The floors were filthy. I wore socks around one day and when I took them off they were dark brown at the bottom. The bedding was the worst part. Reddish-brown stains all over the comforter. We booked 6 days and there was only 1 roll of toilet paper.

Overall I would definitely stay at the hotel again, I just wouldn’t book through Five Star Luxury Travel.

primaryHost.about:
Five Star Luxury Travel was founded in 2013  by Jennifer Restrepo to meet very specific needs in high-end resort living travel.  Five Star Luxury Travel is a unique service that transforms the lives of both vacationers and property owners alike.  Jennifer Restrepo created the company to transform the condo hotel experience for everyone. The company manages the investments of owners, bringing them up to a three times higher return on their investment than they could otherwise get. A 90% occupancy rate is achieved through specialized one-on-one concierge service and a five star management style that keeps condos in top shape.

 

For vacationers, Five Star Luxury Travel provides the ultimate in luxury accommodations and pampering for a fraction of the price. The company caters to both celebrities and those who wish to be treated like such. Five star service is what guests receive with services that go above and beyond including: grocery shopping, transportation, and personalized concierge service that you can’t get from a hotel all while enjoying the full range of activities and amenities the hotel has to offer.

 

For property owners, Five Star Luxury Travel provides security and peace of mind as the company manages every detail related to the property all while charging the lowest management fees. Owners who work with the company see incredible returns on their investment and can rest assured that their property will be taken care of and maintained to the highest standards.
